<font color="#FF0000">RESPONSE TO ANNE</font><br>
<tt>Thu Nov 28  1:27:52 US/Eastern 1996
</tt><p>
Dear Anne:<br><br>
Your biological father probably was not U.S. Air Force.  Most USAF personnel were restricted to base during this time, so contact with &quot;outlying areas&quot; would be minimal.  I don't know how much this helps, but it might narrow the field a bit.  Good luck.<br><br>
One further thought; you might contact either the Pentagon or the different services--they might even be on-line.  I know that the U.S. Coast Guard is on-line, and that it does answer its e-mail.  The others might also.<br><br>
Please also know that I, for one, appreciate that you are here and contributing to our society.  You are a welcome addition.  While I don't know the circumstances of your coming, I imagine it wasn't too much fun in the beginning.  Thank you for having the courage to make this posting.
<p><code>-- searat@sorcom.com  (John C. Ratliff) </code><p>


